OL,5, Victims of sexual harassment at some UK
OL,6, universities will no longer be silenced
OL,7, by "gagging" clauses, as part of a     
OL,8, pledge backed by the government.       
OL,10,FA 2020 BBC News investigation found    
OL,11,Fnearly a third of universities had used
OL,12,Fnon-disclosure agreements (NDAs) to    
OL,13,Fsilence student complaints about sexual
OL,14,Fmisconduct, bullying and harassment.   
OL,16,FNow, the government is asking the more 
OL,17,Fthan 150 universities in the UK not to 
OL,18,Fuse NDAs for such "shabby practice".   
OL,20,FSix have so far signed the pledge.     
